    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p>SSUE TYPE: Story</p>

<p>Summary: Implement autonomous security configuration through AI</p>

<p>Description:</p>

<p>Objective<br/>
The application requires the AI not only to detect vulnerabilities but also to automatically configure security settings to mitigate identified risks.</p>

<p>Context<br/>
Currently, the AI only detects and reports vulnerabilities. This limits the system’s response capability since manual intervention is required to apply corrective measures.</p>

<p>The goal is to evolve the system toward a more autonomous and proactive model.</p>

<p>Scope of Work</p>

<p>David is responsible for:</p>

<ul>
	<li>Designing the logic that allows the AI to automatically apply security configurations.</li>
	<li>Implementing automated response mechanisms for detected vulnerabilities.</li>
	<li>Implementing detailed logging of every action executed by the AI.</li>
	<li>Adding manual mode / autonomous mode switching capability.</li>
	<li>Ensuring rollback capability in case of errors.</li>
	<li>Documenting automation behavior and rules.</li>
</ul>


<p>Acceptance Criteria</p>

<ul>
	<li>The AI can automatically apply security configurations after detecting vulnerabilities.</li>
	<li>All automated actions are logged.</li>
	<li>Autonomous mode can be enabled or disabled.</li>
	<li>No existing functionality is broken.</li>
	<li>Technical documentation is updated.</li>
</ul>


<p>Definition of Done (DoD)</p>

<ul>
	<li>Feature implemented and tested.</li>
	<li>Security testing completed in a controlled environment.</li>
	<li>Code Review approved.</li>
	<li>Validation in development environment completed.</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
